\f0\b\fs26\fsmilli13333 BOTH FLOWS GO THROUGH THE SAME SYSTEM\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 \uc0\u8232 After funds has been escrowed and accepted by either the advertiser when a channel owner applies for a closed campaign or after an advertiser accepts the offers on a listed channel. Every single acceptance comes through one path\u8232 \u8232 Funds get escrowed 
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs26\fsmilli13333 Draft Post, story or whatever format review. 
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs26\fsmilli13333 The channel owner drafts the post using the brief \uc0\u8232 The advertiser approves the draft post
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs26\fsmilli13333 If advertiser doesn\'92t approve, the advertiser makes a comment and gives feedback on the draft post\uc0\u8232 The channel owner makes the correction and sends for review\u8232 Process goes on until advertiser accepts the draft post\u8232 Time is then scheduled for the post
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs26\fsmilli13333 Once the time has been agreed upon, the bot automatically schedules the post to go live at the agreed time\uc0\u8232 Once the post goes live, the post must stay minimum of 24 hours before deal is completed\u8232 If post is deleted, then a message is sent to the channel owner that post has been deleted and campaign cancelled. 
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs26\fsmilli13333 Before post is auto published, the information will be given to the channel owner to make sure to leave the post up for more than 24 hours before the deal can be completed\uc0\u8232 Once the deal has been completed, the funds goes straight to the channel owner\u8232 Only the channel owner can withdraw, or a PR manager that has been given withdrawal permission
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \

\fs26\fsmilli13333 At every step of this flow, the bot reverifies if the user that is currently making an action is still an admin of the channel. Before post is agreed, before time is agreed, before withdrawal\uc0\u8232 \u8232 This will be the combined system for all movement after acceptance\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \u8232 There could also be a settings button or a support button. However, the main functionalities of the mini app have been fully covered in extensive detail. 
